.IX Title "pEFL::Evas::TextblockCursor 3pm"
.TH pEFL::Evas::TextblockCursor 3pm 2022-11-01 "perl v5.38.2" "User Contributed Perl Documentation"
.\" For nroff, turn off justification.  Always turn off hyphenation; it makes
.\" way too many mistakes in technical documents.
.if n .ad l
.nh
.SH NAME
pEFL::Evas::TextblockCursor
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This module is a perl binding to Evas_Textblock_Cursor.
.PP
A pEFL::Evas::TextblockCursor is used to manipulate the cursor of an evas textblock.
.SH "SPECIFICS OF THE BINDING"
.IX Header "SPECIFICS OF THE BINDING"
For the following methods, which return an Eina_List, exist a "perl\-value"\-method:
.ie n .IP $cur\->\fBrange_formats_get_pv()\fR; 4
.el .IP \f(CW$cur\fR\->\fBrange_formats_get_pv()\fR; 4
.IX Item "$cur->range_formats_get_pv();"
.PD 0
.ie n .IP $cur\->\fBrange_geometry_get_pv()\fR; 4
.el .IP \f(CW$cur\fR\->\fBrange_geometry_get_pv()\fR; 4
.IX Item "$cur->range_geometry_get_pv();"
.PD
.PP
Beyond the pure translation of the C\-API, there are some shortcuts-methods:
.ie n .IP "$cur\->text_markup_prepend($text); (for evas_object_textblock_text_markup_prepend($cur,$text);" 4
.el .IP "\f(CW$cur\fR\->text_markup_prepend($text); (for evas_object_textblock_text_markup_prepend($cur,$text);" 4
.IX Item "$cur->text_markup_prepend($text); (for evas_object_textblock_text_markup_prepend($cur,$text);"
.PD 0
.IP pEFL::Evas::TextblockCursor::copy($cur1,$cur2); 4
.IX Item "pEFL::Evas::TextblockCursor::copy($cur1,$cur2);"
.IP pEFL::Evas::TextblockCursor::compare($cur1,$cur2); 4
.IX Item "pEFL::Evas::TextblockCursor::compare($cur1,$cur2);"
.IP pEFL::Evas::TextblockCursor::equal($cur1,$cur2); 4
.IX Item "pEFL::Evas::TextblockCursor::equal($cur1,$cur2);"
.PD
